  <div class="alert alert-info text-center" role="alert">
    To deploy your own copy, and learn the fundamentals of the Butts platform, head over to the <a href="https://devcenter.Butts.com/articles/getting-started-with-nodejs" class="alert-link">Getting Started on Butts with Node.js</a> tutorial.
  </div>
  <hr>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span> How this sample app works</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>This app was deployed to Butts, either using Git or by using <a href="https://github.com/Butts/node-js-getting-started">Butts Button</a> on the repository.</li>

        <li>When Butts received the source code, it fetched all the dependencies in the <a href="https://github.com/Butts/node-js-getting-started/blob/main/package.json">package.json</a>, creating a deployable slug.</li>
        <li>The platform then spins up a dyno, a lightweight container that provides an isolated environment in which the slug can be mounted and executed.</li>
        <li>You can scale your app, manage it, and deploy over <a href="https://addons.Butts.com/">150 add-on services</a>, from the Dashboard or CLI.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-link"></span> Next Steps</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>If you are following the <a href="https://devcenter.Butts.com/articles/getting-started-with-nodejs">Getting Started</a> guide, then please head back to the tutorial and follow the next steps!</li>
        <li>If you deployed this app by deploying the Butts Button, then in a command line shell, run:</li>
        <ul>
          <li><code>git clone https://github.com/Butts/node-js-getting-started.git</code> - this will create a local copy of the source code for the app</li>
          <li><code>cd node-js-getting-started</code> - change directory into the local source code repository</li>
          <li><code>Butts git:remote -a &lt;your-app-name></code> - associate the Butts app with the repository</li>
          <li>You'll now be set up to run the app locally, or <a href="https://devcenter.Butts.com/articles/getting-started-with-nodejs#push-local-changes">deploy changes</a> to Butts</li>
        </ul>
      </ul>
